org.pvg.plasmagraph.utils.template

Class Template

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pvg.plasmagraph.utils.template.Template

  • public class Template
extends java.lang.Object

    Settings container for all of PlasmaGraph.

    Maintains every possible setting that can and will be used in graphing or using the optional tools.

    It is important to note that this class fires events! Therefore, this class should not be made more than once. (This class may be made into a singleton someday, but not yet.)

    Version:
    0.8.4
    Author:
    Plasma Visualization Group

      • Template

        public Template(java.lang.String name,
        ChartType type,
        java.lang.String x,
        java.lang.String y,
        boolean legend,
        boolean tooltips,
        boolean urls,
        org.jfree.chart.plot.PlotOrientation o,
        AxisType x_type,
        AxisType y_type,
        InterpolationType interpolation,
        OutlierResponse outlier,
        double lower,
        double upper,
        int n)

        Constructor for Template objects. Provides user-assigned values to new Template object.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the chart to be created. (String)
        type - ChartType object containing the type of graph to make. (ChartType)
        x - The name of the x axis for the chart to be created. (String)
        y - The name of the y axis for the chart to be created. (String)
        legend - If the legend will be visible on the chart. (boolean)
        tooltips - If tool tips will be available on the chart. (boolean)
        urls - If URLs will be generated for the chart. (boolean)
        o - The orientation of the range axis. (PlotOrientation) [PlotOrientation.HORIZONTAL or PlotOrientation.VERTICAL.]
        x_type - AxisType that the X Axis will use. (AxisType)
        y_type - AxisType that the Y Axis will use. (AxisType)
        interpolation - Type of interpolation that will be performed. (InterpolationType)
        outlier - Type of response that the outlier search will provide. (OutlierResponse)
        lower - Lower bound of the interpolated data. (double)
        upper - Upper bound of the interpolated data. (double)
        n - Number of points to graph in the interpolated data. (int)
